Package cipher

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Caesar
    Class that facilitates the encryption and decryption of a Caesar shift cipher.
    CaesarTest  
    CipherBreakers
    Class that contains all complete cipher decryption stacks.
    CipherBreakersTest  
    CipherTest  
    DetectEnglish
    A class that contains most of the methods to do with the detection of English in decrypted text and the subsequent respacing.
    DetectEnglishTest  
    FileIO
    Class that manages all File IO operations for the project.
    FileIOTest  
    InitialiseStaticResources
    A class to facilitate the generation and updating of all static resources necessary for the project.
    IOC  
    IOCTest  
    KasiskiExamination  
    KasiskiExaminationTest  
    Manager
    A class that handles the management of the decryption of the string passed to the server by each client.
    ManagerTest  
    Mapping
    A class to store fractions of a Simple Substitution Cipher key in a manageable way.
    MultiLemmaAnalysis
    Uses PredictWords to determine what p-equivalent n-grams each part of a string could be.
    MultiLemmaAnalysisTest  
    NGramAnalyser
    A class that is capable of counting the number of given strings of length n that occur in a given string.
    NGramAnalyserTest  
    PredictWords
    A class that is capable of predicting words that are encoded with a simple substitution cipher using character index form to determine pattern-equivalent (or p equivalent n-grams).
    PredictWordsTest  
    ProbableSubstitutions
    A class to facilitate the detection of the most likely decryption key for a cipher-text encrypted with the simple substitution cipher.
    ProbableSubstitutionsTest  
    SearchNode
    A class used in the Monte-Carlo method of solving simple-substitution ciphers in SubstitutionTreeSearch.
    Substitution
    Facilitates encryption and decryption implementing a Simple Substitution Cipher.
    SubstitutionTest  
    SubstitutionTreeSearch
    Class implementing the Monte-Carlo Tree Search for solving substitution ciphers used by the University of Alberta.
    SubstitutionTreeSearchTest  
    Vigenere
    Class to facilitate encryption and decryption using the Vigenere cipher.
    VigenereTest  
    WordGraph
    Class to facilitate the tree search of possible decryptions.
